Dear Dirk,

The colours were black and red because black = 1 and red = 2 in R. The 
trick was that I took the logical variable Fleiss93cont$region=="Europe" 
which is TRUE if the value is "Europe" and FALSE if it is "Asia" or 
whatever. By setting parentheses, this is interpreted as 1 (for 
"Europe") and 0 otherwise. Adding 1 provides 2 (that is red, for 
"Europe") and 1 (that is black) otherwise.

Of course you may set colours as you like. For the given example, you 
may write, e.g.,

cols<- c("green","violet")

to obtain these colours. For coding more than two values you need more 
colours.

Best,

Gerta


